Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
ecoPlace(25.10)                                                ecoPlace(25.10)

Name
       ecoPlace - Incrementally places the unplaced standard cells

Syntax
       ecoPlace

       [-help]

       [-fixPlacedInsts {true|false}]

       [-place_detail_use_GA_filler_groups {true|false}]

       [-reportSpareCells <fileName>]

       [-saveODInfoOnly {true|false}]

       [-timing_driven {true|false}]

       [-useGACells <GACoreSite>]

       [-useGAFillerCells <GAFillerCells>]

       [-useSpareCells {true|false}]

       Incrementally  places  the  unplaced standard cells. For pre-mast flow,
       you need to run ecoPlace without any spare cell and GA filler  options.
       In a pre-mask flow, this command moves the unplaced standard cells into
       the core area. During an ECO loop, some new unplaced standard cells may
       get introduced. If the goal is to move the unplaced standard cells into
       the  core area and place them without disturbing the original placement
       (pre-mask flow), it is recommended to run ecoPlace at this stage.

       The ecoPlace command supports both the GA filler  flow  and  the  spare
       cell  flow  in  the post-mask flow. In a post-mask flow, if you specify
       -useSpareCells, the software can map the unplaced cells to  the  avail-
       able  spare  cells.  Spare  cells  are added by addSpareInstance at the
       placement stage.

       When one of the GA options is provided in a post-mask flow, the command
       can map existing unplaced cells to placed GAFillers in the design.  The
       GA   filler   options  are  -useGACells,  -useGAFillerCells,  place_de-
       tail_use_GA_filler_groups.

       You can use this command after the ecoDefIn  command  when  some  newly
       added cells are still unplaced.

Parameters
       -fixPlacedInsts {true | false}
              Specifies that instances with the PLACED status are not moved.

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each ecoPlace parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man ecoPlace.

       -reportSpareCells <fileName>
              Specifies to report the spare gates that are selected to map the
              unplaced instances. This option works with -useSpareCells only.

       -saveODInfoOnly {true|false}
              Saves the snapshot of the site OD information to the DB.

              * When set to true, it is executed separately  to  save  the  OD
                Info snapshot which is needed for the following ECO flow.

              * When  set  to  false, the snapshot is removed. The DH cell ECO
                flow switches off.

              If there is already a saved snapshot in DB, you can refresh  the
              OD info snapshot by running ecoPlace -saveODInfoOnly true again.

              When  there  is  an  OD  info snapshot inside the DB, checkPlace
              prints the instance info in the report file. However, checkPlace
              will report the violation if you specify the report file. If you
              remove the ODInfo snapshot using ecoPlace -saveODInfoOnly false,
              checkPlace will not check the violation. In case of the OD  mis-
              match  violation, checkPlace will report the following violation
              in the violation browser.

              Instance $inst_name has OD mismatch compared to  the  golden  OD
              info in DH eco flow.

       -timing_driven {true|false}
              Turns on the slack-driven placement for ecoPlace.

              Default: false

       -useGACells <GACoreSite>
              Selects and places the unplaced instances with techSite matching
              the provided GACoreSite. It is expected that there is free space
              to  place the instances. If not, GA fillers could be deleted be-
              fore ecoPlace -useGACells and re-inserted after the command. You
              can use this parameter only for post-mask ECO.

              Note: You cannot specify the -useGAFillerCells parameter if  you
              use this parameter.

       -useGAFillerCells <GAFillerCells>
              Specifies  a list of Gate Array (GA)-style filler cells that the
              tool can replace with GA cells during  post-mask  ECO.  You  can
              only  use  this parameter in a post-mask ECO flow. The new logic
              instances adding during a post-mask flow must already be present
              in the netlist.

              Note: You cannot specify the -useGACells parameter  if  you  use
              this parameter.

       -place_detail_use_GA_filler_groups {true|false}
              Specifies  that  filler  cell instances will only be replaced by
              logic instances that belong to the same GA groups.

              This option can only be used when there is a filler  group  cre-
              ated     by     createGAFillerGroup.     ecoPlace     -place_de-
              tail_use_GA_filler_groups first finds the optimal  location  for
              each  instance  based on its connectivity, then searches for the
              nearest GA filler cell that  is  included  in  the  same  filler
              group,  places  a GA cell at the GA filler location, and deletes
              the original GA filler.

              If the GA cell is smaller than the GA filler, the placer creates
              a new GA filler instance using the list of GA  filler  cells  in
              the same filler group and places the filler in the gap.

              If there is only one filler group created, it equals to ecoPlace
              - useGAFillerCells.

              Default: false

       -useSpareCells {true | false}
              Maps  unplaced  cells  to  spare  cells during placement. First,
              checks whether all  unplaced  cells  match  spare  cells.  Next,
              chooses  a  spare  cell and changes the connections from the un-
              placed cell to the selected spare cell. Finally, deletes the un-
              placed cell. You can use this parameter only for post-mask ECO.

              This option observes the power domain when selecting  the  spare
              cell  and  maps  an unplaced cell to the spare cell in the power
              domain, based on the instance name of the cell. For example,  if
              module A/B is defined for power domain PD2, this option will map
              an unplaced cell A/B/inst1 to a spare cell in module A/B.

              Default: false

Examples
              * The following command performs incremental placement:

                ecoPlace -useSpareCells true

              *

                The   flowing  command  places  the  GA-ECO  cells  on  GACORE
                site.ecoPlace -useGACells GACoreSite

              *

                The following command places GA-ECO cells on the specified GA-
                Fillers and fills remaining gaps with GA-Fillers.

                ecoPlace -useGAFillerCells {GAFiller1 GAFiller2 ...}

              *

                The following commands create GA Filler group that  associates
                GA-Function  cells  with GA-Fillers. Then, ecoPlace will place
                GA-ECO cells on same group GA-Fillers.

                createGAFillerGroup   -group   GROUP1   -ga_cells    {GA_Cell1
                GA_Cell2... } -ga_fillers {GA_Filler1 GA_Filler2...}

                ecoPlace -place_detail_use_GA_filler_groups true

Related Information
              * addSpareInstance

              * checkPlace

              * createGAFillerGroup

              * ecoDefIn

              * ecoOaDesign

